PLACEHOLDER CERTIFICATE
This is a placeholder certificate file. Replace this with your actual backend
SSL certificate in PEM format before deploying to production.

To obtain your backend certificate:
1. Connect to your backend server: openssl s_client -connect api.finance.example.com:443
2. Copy the certificate between BEGIN CERTIFICATE and END CERTIFICATE
3. Save it to this file

For testing purposes, you can disable certificate pinning by calling:
ApiClient().initialize(enableCertificatePinning: false);
-----END CERTIFICATE-----
